# Normalize line endings. Markdown and text use LF; shell/python scripts force LF.
* text=auto eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.py text eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf
*.command text eol=lf

# Windows batch files keep CRLF
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf

# Binary files
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.pdf binary
*.ico binary

# --- Concurrent-session safety: append-only logs use git's built-in `union` merge
# driver. On a rebase/merge conflict, git keeps BOTH sides (no manual resolution,
# no lost session block); compaction/reconcile dedups + re-sorts afterward. This
# turns the #1 cross-session collision (everyone prepending to session-log.md) into
# a non-event. Do NOT apply union to structured files (project-context.md) — there
# it would corrupt sections; those reconcile deliberately.
06-context/session-log.md merge=union
06-context/audit-log.md merge=union
